em%20like%20a%20burden%20if%20you're%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20retirement%2C%20but%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20it's%20worth%20focusing%20on%20your%20retirement%20savings%20as%20your%20first%20priority.%3Cp%3ETyler%20Le%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIt's%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20pay%20off%20high-interest%20debts%20quickly%2C%20but%20that's%20not%20true%20of%20all%20debt.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIt's%20usually%20better%20to%20not%20highly%20prioritize%20paying%20off%20your%20mortgage%20versus%20saving%20for%20retirement.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThis%20article%20is%20part%20of%C2%A0%26quot%3BThe%20Finish%20Line%2C%26quot%3B%C2%A0a%20series%20that%20offers%20advice%20and%20answers%20burning%20questions%20about%20retirement%20planning.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20certified%20financial%20planner%2C%20the%20most%20pressing%20concern%20I%20see%20among%20people%20preparing%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fretirement-calculator%5C%22%3Eretirement%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20whether%20they%20have%20enough%20money%20saved.%20The%20second%20most%20common%20concern%20people%20have%20is%20paying%20off%20all%20their%20debt%20and%20reducing%20their%20monthly%20overhead%20as%20much%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20many%20fail%20to%20realize%20is%20that%20by%20focusing%20solely%20on%20aggressive%20debt%20payback%2C%20they%20are%20further%20limiting%20the%20funds%20they%20have%20to%20put%20toward%20building%20a%20retirement%20nest%20egg.%20By%20opting%20to%20aggressively%20pay%20down%20debt%20instead%20of%20investing%2C%20they%20create%20a%20negatively%20reinforced%20cycle%20of%20insufficient%20savings.%20That%20means%20they%20add%20less%20money%20to%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fbest-retirement-plans%5C%22%3Eretirement%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20means%20additional%20financial%20stress%20and%20more%20financial%20instability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20truth%20is%20that%20not%20all%20debt%20in%20retirement%20is%20a%20bad%20thing.%20It's%20important%20to%20consider%20the%20type%20of%20debt%20and%20consider%20whether%20you%20should%20prioritize%20paying%20off%20debt%20or%20saving%20in%20the%20final%20years%20before%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAggressively%20pay%20off%20high-interest%20credit%20card%20debt%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-score%2Fwhat-is-high-interest-debt%5C%22%3EHigh-interest%20credit%20card%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E%20(10%25%20in%20APR%20or%20more)%20is%20the%20only%20type%20I%20would%20recommend%20aggressively%20paying%20off.%20You'll%20want%20to%20list%20out%20each%20of%20your%20debts%2C%20the%20interest%20rate%2C%20and%20the%20monthly%20payment%20amount.%20Then%20you%20should%20make%20a%20plan%20to%20pay%20it%20off%20before%20retirement%2C%20utilizing%20either%20the%20debt%20snowball%20or%20avalanche%20based%20on%20your%20personal%20preference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20are%20a%20fan%20of%20quick%20wins%2C%20then%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fdebt-snowball-vs-debt-avalanche%5C%22%3Edebt%20snowball%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20your%20best%20bet.%20If%20you%20really%20want%20to%20quickly%20free%20up%20more%20monthly%20cash%20flow%2C%20then%20choose%20the%20debt%20avalanche%2C%20as%20it%20pays%20off%20the%20cards%20with%20the%20highest%20monthly%20payment%20and%20largest%20balance%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EYour%20student%20loan%20plan%20should%20depend%20on%20several%20factors%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20student%20loans%2C%20whether%20you%20prioritize%20repayment%20before%20retirement%20will%20largely%20depend%20on%20the%20interest%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20they%20are%20federal%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fstudent-loans%2Fbest-private-student-loans%5C%22%3Eprivate%20student%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%20higher%20interest%20rate%20(8%25%20or%20higher)%2C%20I%20recommend%20aggressively%20paying%20off%20those%20loans%20before%20retirement%20while%20continuing%20to%20save.%20If%20your%20student%20loans%20are%20less%20than%208%25%2C%20I%20would%20continue%20making%20regular%20payments%20and%20investing%20at%20the%20same%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20your%20student%20loans%20are%20in%20default%2C%20please%20be%20sure%20to%20work%20on%20getting%20them%20current%20before%20you%20retire.%20Contrary%20to%20popular%20belief%2C%20they%20do%20not%20simply%20go%20away%20after%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20time%20has%20passed.%20The%20federal%20government%20will%20actually%20garnish%20a%20portion%20of%20your%20Social%20Security%20check%20to%20ensure%20they%20are%20paid%20%E2%80%94%20furthering%20your%20personal%20retirement%20insecurity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EYour%20mortgage%20doesn't%20need%20to%20be%20a%20top%20priority%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20recommend%20aggressively%20paying%20down%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fbest-mortgage-lenders-first-time-buyers%5C%22%3Emortgage%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20retirement%20unless%20you%20have%20saved%20enough%20for%20retirement%20and%20have%20substantial%20cash%20flow.%20While%20you%20spend%20time%2C%20energy%2C%20and%20capital%20funneling%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20into%20an%20illiquid%20asset%2C%20you%20could%20have%20put%20that%20money%20into%20your%20retirement%20account%20and%20secure%20a%20fantastic%20standard%20of%20living%20in%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFailing%20to%20save%20enough%20for%20retirement%20presents%20a%20large%20risk%20for%20many%20Americans.%20Inflation%20and%20wage%20stagnation%20can%20make%20it%20hard%20to%20save%20for%20retirement.%20However%20much%20debt%20might%20bother%20you%20emotionally%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20remember%20that%20it%20is%20more%20important%20to%20have%20a%20nest%20egg%20to%20fall%20back%20on%20than%20it%20is%20to%20have%20a%20paid-off%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20to%20decide%20your%20priorities%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20financial%20gurus%20recommend%20only%20focusing%20on%20one%20financial%20priority%20at%20a%20time%2C%20but%20you%20can%20truly%20invest%20and%20pay%20down%20debt%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20In%20my%20experience%2C%20it%20is%20the%20most%20sustainable%20path.%20But%20how%20do%20you%20decide%20which%20is%20the%20most%20important%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20your%20interest%20rate%20on%20your%20debt%20is%20less%20than%20your%20expected%20rate%20of%20return%20on%20your%20investments%2C%20you%20should%20invest%20instead%20of%20aggressively%20paying%20off%20debt.%20If%20your%20investment%20return%20is%20lower%20than%20the%20interest%20rate%20on%20your%20debt%2C%20prioritizing%20debt%20payoff%20makes%20the%20most%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20if%20your%20car%20note%20has%20an%20interest%20rate%20of%204%25%2C%20but%20your%20investment%20annual%20expected%20return%20is%208%25%2C%20you%20will%20be%20better%20off%20financially%20if%20you%20invest%20more%20instead%20of%20paying%20down%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFocus%20more%20on%20your%20retirement%20savings%20as%20you%20approach%20retirement%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20are%20less%20than%2010%20years%20from%20retirement%20and%20have%20less%20than%20five%20times%20your%20annual%20income%20saved%20in%20retirement%2C%20then%20you%20will%20want%20to%20prioritize%20putting%20money%20away%20for%20retirement%20over%20anything%20else%20(except%20maybe%20high-interest%20credit%20card%20debt%20or%20payday%20loans).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20let's%20say%20you%20make%20%2475%2C000%20annually.%20If%20you%20have%20less%20than%20%24375%2C000%20saved%20across%20your%20various%20retirement%20accounts%2C%20then%20you%20will%20want%20to%20heavily%20prioritize%20your%20retirement%20savings.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20there%20is%20nothing%20more%20valuable%20to%20you%20than%20getting%20as%20much%20money%20as%20you%20can%20in%20your%20retirement%20accounts%20so%20that%20compounding%20can%20work%20its%20magic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20the%20wisest%20decision%2C%20it's%20best%20to%20first%20evaluate%20your%20personal%20financial%20situation%2C%20consider%20your%20debts%20and%20retirement%20accounts%2C%20and%20calculate%20how%20much%20you%20need%20to%20save%20to%20maintain%20your%20standard%20of%20living%20in%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20in%20March%202023.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fplanning-retirement-still-have-debt-pay-off-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730933520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F641cc02fd67fe70018a37f29%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fplanning-retirement-still-have-debt-pay-off-2024-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Debt%20can%20seem%20like%20a%20huge%20burden%20if%20you're%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20retirement%2C%20but%20it%20may%20be%20worth%20focusing%20on%20your%20retirement%20savings%20as%20your%20first%20priority.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Anna%20N'Jie-Konte)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fplanning-retirement-still-have-debt-pay-off-2024-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Scot%20gets%20dream%20job%20as%20lighthouse%20keeper%20on%20remote%20Australian%20island%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730933468000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2Ffe73%2Flive%2F0da60680-9a8f-11ef-82c3-45a801b7330b.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcgk1x7kv2kko%233%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sandy%20Duthie's%20%26quot%3Bdream%20job%26quot%3B%20involves%20sol