C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fhow-does-fed-impact-mortgage-rates%5C%22%3Ehow%20the%20relationship%20between%20mortgages%20and%20the%20Fed%20works%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20right%20now%2C%20there%20are%20other%20forces%20keeping%20mortgage%20rates%20high%2C%20even%20as%20the%20Fed%20gears%20up%20to%20lower%20rates%20again.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20Fed%20cut%20probably%20won't%20have%20much%20of%20an%20impact%20on%20mortgage%20rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20often%20move%20up%20or%20down%20ahead%20of%20expected%20Fed%20moves.%20But%20once%20the%20market%20expectations%20are%20set%2C%20they%20typically%20don't%20change%20unless%20the%20Fed%20surprises%20everyone.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20market%20is%20basically%20fully%20pricing%20in%20a%2025-basis-point%20cut%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Emanuel%20Santa-Donato%2C%20senior%20vice%20president%20and%20chief%20market%20analyst%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftomo.com%2F%5C%22%3ETomo%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BMarkets%20only%20react%20when%20they%20get%20things%20different%20than%20they%20expect.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20will%20also%20be%20closely%20watching%20Fed%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell's%20press%20conference%20following%20the%20meeting%20for%20clues%20as%20to%20what%20the%20central%20bank%20might%20do%20at%20future%20meetings.%20Any%20change%20from%20the%20current%20outlook%2C%20which%20is%20that%20the%20Fed%20will%20continue%20to%20slowly%20lower%20rates%20through%20the%20rest%20of%20this%20year%20and%20in%202025%2C%20could%20cause%20mortgage%20rates%20to%20fluctuate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAny%20additional%20guidance%20provided%20might%20move%20mortgage%20rates%2C%20but%20the%20cut%20itself%20is%20not%20really%20going%20to%20do%20anything%20one%20way%20or%20another%2C%26quot%3B%20Santa-Donato%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20mortgage%20rates%20are%20so%20high%20right%20now%3A%20The%20economy%2C%20the%20Fed%2C%20and%20the%20election%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESanta-Donato%20says%20that%20one%20of%20the%20main%20forces%20impacting%20mortgage%20rates%20right%20now%20isn't%20the%20upcoming%20Fed%20meeting%2C%20but%20rather%20market%20expectations%20of%20high%20inflation%20now%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-wins-presidential-election-race-2024-11%5C%22%3EFormer%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20has%20won%20the%20presidency%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20market%20over%20the%20past%20month%20has%20increasingly%20been%20pricing%20in%20a%20Donald%20Trump%20victory%20and%20Republican%20sweep%2C%20and%20the%20market%20believes%2C%20based%20on%20the%20policies%20that%20party%20has%20outlined%2C%20that%20is%20going%20to%20be%20the%20most%20inflationary%20outcome%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20economy%20has%20been%20surprisingly%20resilient%20this%20year%2C%20which%20has%20shifted%20investor%20expectations%20around%20future%20Fed%20cuts.%20Selma%20Hepp%2C%20the%20chief%20economist%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.corelogic.com%2F%5C%22%3ECoreLogic%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20says%20that%20markets%20initially%20overestimated%20how%20much%20the%20Fed%20would%20cut%20rates%20after%20its%2050-basis-point%20cut%20in%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20had%20that%20initial%2050-basis-point%20and%20I%20think%20markets%20may%20have%20expected%20at%20that%20point%20that%20you'd%20have%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20Hepp%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20then%20when%20the%20job%20report%20and%20the%20inflation%20report%20came%20in%2C%20there%20was%20sort%20of%20that%20step%20back%20realizing%20that%20things%20are%20still%20not%20falling%20off%20the%20cliff%20and%20we%20still%20have%20a%20really%20strong%20economy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20could%20see%20mortgage%20rates%20ease%20next%20year%20as%20the%20Fed%20continues%20cutting%20rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20is%20expected%20to%20continue%20lowering%20rates%20next%20year%2C%20which%20should%20help%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fwill-mortgage-rates-go-down-this-year%5C%22%3Emortgage%20rates%20go%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202025.%20But%20how%20much%20they'll%20fall%20depends%20on%20the%20economy%2C%20whether%20the%20labor%20market%20continues%20to%20cool%20off%2C%20and%20how%20inflation%20trends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20do%20think%20mortgage%20rates%20will%20come%20down%2C%20maybe%20not%20as%20much%20as%20we%20were%20hoping%2C%26quot%3B%20Hepp%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20maybe%206%25%20is%20the%20sort%20of%20benchmark%20around%20which%20mortgage%20rates%20will%20oscillate%2C%20whereas%20we%20were%20hoping%20to%20get%20maybe%20to%205.5%25%20to%205.75%25%20by%20the%20end%20of%20next%20year.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20inflation%20reignites%2C%20that%20could%20keep%20rates%20near%20their%20current%20levels%20or%20even%20cause%20them%20to%20rise%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20federal%20government%20promotes%20inflationary%20policies%2C%20the%20reaction%20of%20the%20Fed%20could%20be%20to%20raise%20rates%20and%20try%20to%20get%20that%20inflation%20under%20control%2C%26quot%3B%20Santa-Donato%20says.%20%26quot%3BThat%20would%20push%20mortgage%20rates%20higher.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20this%20means%20for%20homebuyers%20and%20homeowners%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20mortgage%20rates%20are%20high%20and%20likely%20to%20remain%20elevated%20at%20least%20through%20the%20end%20of%20this%20year%2C%20it%20could%20still%20be%20worth%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fhow-to-buy-a-house-step-by-step-guide%5C%22%3Ebuying%20a%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20now%20if%20you're%20ready.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHepp%20points%20out%20that%20buyers%20can%20often%20get%20better%20deals%20on%20homes%20in%20the%20winter.%20So%20even%20though%20you%20might%20not%20get%20a%20low%20mortgage%20rate%2C%20you%20could%20find%20a%20lower-priced%20