nce%2075%25%20of%20its%20exports%20go%20to%20the%20US%2C%20as%20well%20as%20thousands%20of%20people%20pouring%20north%20across%20the%20US%20border%2C%20analysts%20and%20economists%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20victory%20adds%20to%20Trudeau's%20trouble%20at%20a%20time%20polls%20show%20he%20would%20likely%20lose%20to%20his%20Conservative%20opponent%20in%20an%20election%20that%20must%20be%20held%20within%20a%20year.%20Canada's%20slowing%20economy%20and%20a%20rapid%20surge%20in%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%20are%20top%20campaign%20issues%2C%20which%20come%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20diplomatic%20disputes%20with%20China%20and%20India%20that%20have%20hampered%20efforts%20to%20diversify%20trade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECanada%2C%20the%20world's%20No.%204%20crude%20oil%20producer%2C%20is%20especially%20vulnerable%20to%20Trump's%20plan%20for%20a%2010%25%20tariff%20on%20all%20imports%20and%20his%20vow%20to%20boost%20US%20energy%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELaura%20Dawson%20of%20the%20Future%20Borders%20Coalition%2C%20which%20seeks%20to%20smooth%20bilateral%20trade%20and%20travel%2C%20said%20the%20real%20challenge%20will%20be%20gradually%20declining%20investor%20confidence%20in%20America's%20northern%20neighbour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%C2%A0Canada%2C%20four%20years%20of%20a%20Trump%20presidency%20could%20be%20very%20long%20indeed%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20called%20Trudeau%20%26quot%3Ba%20far-left%20lunatic%26quot%3B%20in%202022%20for%20requiring%20truck%20drivers%20crossing%20the%20border%20to%20be%20vaccinated%20against%20COVID-19.%20In%20June%202018%2C%20Trump%20walked%20out%20of%20a%20G7%20summit%20in%20Quebec%20and%20blasted%20the%20Canadian%20leader%20for%20being%20%26quot%3Bvery%20dishonest%20and%20weak.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrudeau%2C%20who%20has%20been%20in%20power%20since%202015%2C%20congratulated%20Trump%20on%20Wednesday%20and%20said%20the%20friendship%20between%20the%20two%20nations%20was%20the%20envy%20of%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20know%20President%20Trump%20and%20I%20will%20work%20together%20to%20create%20more%20opportunity%2C%20prosperity%2C%20and%20security%20for%20both%20of%20our%20nations%2C%26quot%3B%20Trudeau%20said%20on%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20Trump's%20win%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20Finance%20Minister%20Chrystia%20Freeland%20sought%20to%20reassure%20Canadians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20Canadians%20were%20anxious%20throughout%20the%20night%20and%20I%20want%20to%20say%20...%20that%20Canada%20will%20be%20absolutely%20fine%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20strong%20relationship%20with%20the%20United%20States%2C%20we%20have%20a%20strong%20relationship%20with%20President%20Trump%20and%20his%20team.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20however%2C%20Trudeau%20told%20reporters%20another%20Trump%20presidency%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Ba%20step%20back%26quot%3B%20that%20made%20life%20tough%20for%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDesjardins%20Economics%20analysts%20forecast%20Trump's%20policies%20would%20result%20in%20real%20Canadian%20gross%20domestic%20product%20falling%20by%201.7%25%20by%20end-2028%20compared%20to%20what%20would%20have%20happened%20under%20a%20Democratic%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Canadian%20Chamber%20of%20Commerce%20said%20Trump's%20planned%2010%25%20tariff%20would%20cut%20Canada's%20real%20income%20by%200.9%25%20annually%20and%20labor%20productivity%20by%20nearly%201%25.%20If%20other%20countries%20retaliate%2C%20setting%20off%20a%20trade%20war%2C%20real%20income%20would%20drop%20by%201.5%25%20annually%2C%20with%20labor%20productivity%20falling%20by%20nearly%201.6%25%20each%20year%2C%20the%20chamber%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20first%20took%20office%20in%202017%20vowing%20to%20renegotiate%20the%20North%20American%20Free%20Trade%20Agreement%2C%20the%20trilateral%20trade%20deal%20with%20Mexico%20and%20Canada%2C%20complaining%20that%20trading%20partners%20were%20taking%20advantage%20of%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%2018%20months%20of%20sometimes%20rancorous%20talks%2C%20which%20at%20one%20point%20saw%20the%20United%20States%20and%20Canada%20imposing%20sanctions%20on%20each%20other's%20products%2C%20the%20pact%20was%20reborn%20as%20the%20US-Mexico-Canada%20(USMCA)%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20said%20on%20Oct.%2011%20he%20would%20use%20an%20existing%20USMCA%20clause%20to%20start%20renegotiating%20the%20treaty%20in%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20going%20to%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20fun%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERECESSION%20INDUCING%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDavid%20Doyle%2C%20Macquarie's%20head%20of%20economics%20for%20the%20Americas%2C%20said%20Trump's%20promised%20policies%20had%20the%20potential%20to%20be%20a%20significant%20economic%20shock%20for%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20possible%20that%20it%20is%20a%20recession-inducing%20event%20because%20it's%20on%20such%20an%20enormous%20scale%20that%20we%20really%20haven't%20seen%20for%20almost%20100%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECanada%20staved%20off%20the%20worst%20during%20the%20USMCA%20talks%20by%20proactively%20sending%20officials%20and%20politicians%20to%20dozens%20of%20US%20states%20to%20highlight%20the%20benefits%20of%20free%20trade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKirsten%20Hillman%2C%20the%20long-serving%20Canadian%20ambassador%20in%20Washington%2C%20said%20Canada%20has%20%26quot%3Ba%20very%20good%20ability%20to%20push%20back%26quot%3B%20on%20the%2010%25%20tariff%20proposal%20and%20had%20already%20been%20talking%20to%20Trump's%20camp%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20spending%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20talking%20to%20the%20Trump%20team%2C%20his%20advisers%2C%20saying%20...%20this%20just%20isn't%20the%20right%20move%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20the%20Canadian%20Broadcasting%20Corp.%20in%20mid-October.%3C%2Fp%3E%5C