ds%20-%20raising%20%241%20billion%20in%20less%20than%20three%20months%20-%20and%20drew%20endorsements%20from%20celebrities%20ranging%20from%20pop%20star%20Taylor%20Swift%20to%20actor%20and%20former%20California%20Governor%20Arnold%20Schwarzenegger.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Harris'%20campaign%20ultimately%20failed%20to%20overcome%20deep-seated%20voter%20concerns%20about%20inflation%20and%20immigration%20-%20twin%20issues%20that%20opinion%20polls%20showed%20favored%20Trump.%20Her%20loss%20underscores%20a%20profound%20shift%20in%20American%20politics%20over%20the%20past%20decade%20as%20blue-collar%20voters%20have%20turned%20increasingly%20Republican%20-%20a%20trend%20Trump%20appears%20to%20have%20accelerated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarris%20also%20struggled%20to%20counter%20another%20Trump-era%20trend%3A%20a%20torrent%20of%20misinformation%20unprecedented%20in%20modern%20U.S.%20elections.%20An%20avalanche%20of%20misrepresentations%20and%20falsehoods%20about%20her%20record%20was%20spread%20by%20the%20former%20president%20and%20amplified%20on%20right-wing%20websites%20and%20media%2C%20including%20conspiracy%20theories%20on%20issues%20ranging%20from%20migrant%20crime%20to%20voter%20fraud.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20by%20Reuters%20during%20the%20race%20about%20misinformation%20amplified%20by%20Trump%2C%20his%20campaign%20officials%20typically%20either%20repeated%20the%20falsehoods%20or%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20early%20Wednesday%20morning%2C%20Trump%20had%20won%20279%20electoral%20votes%20to%20Harris'%20223%2C%20with%20several%20states%20yet%20to%20be%20counted.%20This%20account%20of%20how%20Harris%20lost%20is%20based%20on%20Reuters%20interviews%20with%20Harris%20campaign%20staffers%2C%20White%20House%20officials%2C%20Democratic%20Party%20advisors%20and%20close%20allies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20always%20going%20to%20be%20a%20heavy%20lift.%20The%20U.S.%20has%20only%20once%20elected%20a%20president%20-%20Barack%20Obama%20in%202008%20and%202012%20-%20who%20wasn't%20a%20white%20man.%20As%20the%20daughter%20of%20an%20Indian%20mother%20and%20Jamaican%20father%2C%20Harris%20had%20risen%20higher%20in%20the%20country's%20leadership%20than%20any%20other%20woman.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20other%20woman%20to%20get%20as%20close%20as%20she%20did%20-%20Hillary%20Clinton%2C%20defeated%20by%20Trump%20in%202016%20-%20staked%20her%20candidacy%20in%20part%20on%20becoming%20the%20first%20female%20president.%20In%20the%20wake%20of%20Clinton's%20loss%2C%20Harris%20resisted%20putting%20her%20identity%20at%20the%20center%20of%20her%20campaign%2C%20said%20close%20aides%20and%20advisors.%20Instead%2C%20she%20tried%20to%20galvanize%20voters%20on%20issues%20that%20mattered%20to%20women%20and%20Black%20voters%20in%20the%20election%20-%20from%20abortion%20rights%20to%20middle-class%20tax%20cuts%20and%20housing%20affordability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20those%20messages%20struggled%20to%20break%20through%20at%20a%20time%20when%20many%20voters%20were%20fixated%20on%20rising%20consumer%20prices%20during%20the%20first%20three%20years%20of%20the%20Biden%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDespite%20fairly%20strong%20economic%20growth%2C%20especially%20after%20a%20major%20global%20pandemic%2C%20most%20Americans%20weren't%20feeling%20like%20they%20were%20getting%20ahead%20economically%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Melissa%20Deckman%2C%20a%20political%20scientist%20and%20chief%20executive%20of%20Public%20Religion%20Research%20Institute%2C%20a%20nonpartisan%20research%20firm.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Harris%20campaign%20did%20not%20necessarily%20do%20a%20good%20job%20of%20explaining%20how%20her%20policies%20would%20help%20the%20middle%20class%2C%20or%20at%20least%20that%20message%20wasn't%20really%20resonating%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20voters.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20majority%20of%20voters%20said%20they%20trust%20Trump%20more%20to%20handle%20the%20economy%2C%20with%2051%25%20saying%20they%20did%20so%20compared%20to%2047%25%20for%20Harris%2C%20according%20to%20a%20preliminary%20national%20exit%20poll%20conducted%20by%20data%20provider%20Edison%20Research.%20And%20the%20voters%20who%20identified%20the%20economy%20as%20their%20primary%20concern%20voted%20overwhelmingly%20for%20Trump%20over%20Harris%20-%2079%25%20to%2020%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20economy%20proved%20to%20be%20a%20much%20bigger%20concern%20among%20voters%20than%20reproductive%20rights%2C%20with%2031%25%20of%20voters%20saying%20the%20economy%20mattered%20most%20in%20deciding%20how%20to%20vote%20compared%20with%2014%25%20who%20cited%20abortion.%20The%20election%20also%20saw%20a%20large%20gender%20gap.%20Harris%20won%2054%25%20of%20women%20voters%20in%20the%20country%2C%20while%20Trump%20won%2044%25%2C%20the%20preliminary%20exit%20polls%20showed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Harris%20and%20Trump%20campaigns%20and%20the%20White%20House%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAmerica%20has%20given%20us%20an%20unprecedented%20and%20powerful%20mandate%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said%20early%20on%20Wednesday%20to%20a%20roaring%20crowd%20of%20supporters%20at%20the%20Palm%20Beach%20County%20Convention%20Center.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EELECTORAL%20GOLD%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20election%20was%20punctuated%20by%20dramatic%20twists%2C%20including%20two%20assassination%20attempts%20against%20Trump%20and%20the%20stunning%20decision%20by%20Biden%20to%20abandon%20his%20re-election%20bid%20on%20July%2021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDemocrats%20coalesced%20behind%20Harris%20with%20astonishing%20speed%2C%20locking%20up%20her%20party's%20nomination%20within%20two%20weeks%2C%20excited%20by%20her%20potential%20to%20flip%20the%20generational%20argument%20on%20Trump.%20Two%20decades%20her%20senior%2C%20Trump%20had%20successfully%20cast%20the%2081-year-old%20Biden%20as%20a%20frail%20and%20confused%20old%20man.%20She%20would%20turn%20that%20on%20its%20head%2C%20many%20Democrats%20hoped.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20Democratic%20strategists%20questioned%20the%20wisdom%20of%20one%20of%20her%20first%20big%20decisions%3A%20picking%20Minnesota%20Governor%20Tim%20Walz%20as%20running%20mate%20over%20Pennsylvania%20Governor%20Josh%20Shapiro%2C%20a%20deft%20speaker%20with%20proven%20political%20strength%20in%20a%20must-win%20state.%20Her%20campaign%20had%20hoped%20the%20gun-owning%20Walz%2C%20a%20liberal%20policy%20champion%20and%20plain-speaking%20National%20Guardsman%20from%20the%20Midwest%2C%20would%20help%20her%20win%20over%20rural%20white%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWalz%20had%20generated%20buzz%20before%20Harris%20picked%20him%20by%20branding%20Trump%20and%20his%20running%20mate%2C%20Senator%20JD%20Vance%20of%20Ohio%2C%20as%20%26quot%3Bweird%26quot%3B%20on%20national%20television%20in%20July%2C%20winning%20Democratic%20hearts%20and%20media%20attention.%20Later%2C%20though%2C%20Walz%20gained%20unwelcome%20attention%20for%20misstatements%20of%20his%20biography%2C%20including%20his%20military%20service%2C%20and%20for%20an%20uneven%20debate%20performance%20against%20Vance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWalz%20and%20Vance%20didn't%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20Harris%20campaign%20believed%20her%20signature%20issues%20-%20reproductive%20rights%20and%20Trump's%20divisiveness%20-%20would%20energize%20a%20coalition%20of%20women%2C%20Black%20voters%2C%20young%20Americans%2C%20independents%20and%20%26quot%3BNever%20Trump%26quot%3B%20Republicans%2C%20sweeping%20her%20to%20the%20White%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%20before%20the%20race%20began%2C%20Harris%20emerged%20as%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20abortion%20rights.%20When%20the%20U.S.%20Supreme%20Court%20in%202022%20officially%20reversed%20Roe%20v.%20Wade%2C%20declaring%20the%20constitutional%20right%20to%20abortion%20no%20longer%20existed%2C%20the%20setback%20for%20women's%20reproductive%20rights%20created%20an%20unexpected%20opening%20for%20Harris.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20catapulted%20her%20from%20the%20political%20periphery%20into%20the%20heart%20of%20America's%20culture%20wars.%20Opinion%20polls%20showed%20most%20Americans%20disapproved%20of%20the%20court's%20decision%20-%20and%20Harris%20became%20the%20face%20of%20an%20issue%20that%20Democratic%20strategists%20saw%20as%20electoral%20gold.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%20time%20in%20Biden's%20presidency%2C%20he%20handed%20a%20decisive%20issue%20entirely%20to%20his%20vice%20president.%20She%20went%20on%20the%20road%2C%20speaking%20forcefully%20on%20a%20subject%20that%20played%20an%20outsized%20role%20in%20helping%20Democrats%20stave%20off%20an%20expected%20bloodbath%20in%20the%202022%20congressional%20elections.%20After%20the%20midterms%2C%20with%20the%20Democrats%20having%20held%20the%20Senate%20and%20swung%20to%20a%20slight%20minority%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Representatives%2C%20Harris%20was%20now%20seen%20as%20a%20viable%20future%20leader%20in%20the%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20even%20after%20Biden%20stepped%20aside%2C%20concerns%20lingered%20among%20some%20top%20White%20House%20aides%20over%20the%20former%20San%20Francisco%20district%20attorney's%20political%20skills%20-%20including%20a%20perception%20that%20she%20hadn't%20made%20a%20mark%20as%20VP%2C%20her%20short-lived%20campaign%20for%20the%202020%20Democratic%20nomination%20and%20her%20limited%20experience%20courting%20conservative%20voters%20in%20battleground%20states.%20Some%20also%20questioned%20whether%20she%20could%20overcome%20the%20long%20history%20of%20racial%20and%20gender%20discrimination%20in%20the%20U.S.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20securing%20the%20nomination%2C%20Harris%20initially%20put%20many%20of%20those%20concerns%20to%20rest.%20She%20revitalized%20a%20beleaguered%20Democratic%20campaign%2C%20attracting%20record-high%20funding%20and%20a%20groundswell%20of%20support.%20She%20soon%20moved%20ahead%20of%20Trump%20in%20the%20polls%2C%20a%20sign%20she%20was%20sparking%20enthusiasm%20among%20voters%2C%20particularly%20among%20women.%20Trump%20had%20previously%20been%20seen%20as%20the%20front-runner%2C%20partly%20based%20on%20his%20perceived%20strength%20on%20the%20economy%20after%20several%20years%20of%20high%20inflation%20under%20Biden.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20aced%20her%20first%20big%20test%20-%20a%20Sept.%2010%20televised%20debate%20against%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Harris's%20team%20prepared%20for%20what%20would%20be%20her%20only%20in-person%20face-off%20with%20Trump%2C%20they%20focused%20on%20ways%20to%20unnerve%20the%20former%20president%20and%20draw%20attention%20to%20his%20frequent%20falsehoods%20on%20policies%2C%20according%20to%20several%20aides%20involved%20in%20the%20preparations.%20Harris%20holed%20up%20in%20Pittsburgh%20with%20advisers%20and%20conducted%20mock%20debates%20for%20the%20prime-time%20showdown%2C%20the%20aides%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20strategy%20paid%20off.%20Harris%20appeared%20to%20get%20under%20her%20rival's%20skin%20during%20the%20debate.%20She%20pressed%20Trump%20on%20the%20economy%2C%20Ukraine%2C%20healthcare%2C%20the%20January%202021%20Capitol%20riots%20and%20abortion%2C%20leaving%20him%20rattled%20and%20struggling%20to%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFundraising%20spiked%3A%20Her%20campaign%20said%20it%20raised%20%2447%20million%20in%20the%2024%20hours%20after%20the%20debate.%20Most%20voters%20thought%20Harris%20had%20won%2C%20polls%20showed.%20Trump%20shot%20down%20offers%20for%20another%20debate%2C%20claiming%20he'd%20already%20beaten%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20campaign%20trail%2C%20Harris%20mocked%20Trump's%20debate%20performance%2C%20including%20his%20comment%20that%20he%20had%20%26quot%3Bconcepts%20of%20a%20plan%26quot%3B%20to%20replace%20a%20federal%20health%20care%20law.%20As%20she%20gained%20in%20polls%2C%20Harris'%20campaign%20believed%20she%20was%20opening%20up%20states%20that%20had%20been%20out%20of%20reach%20for%20Biden%2C%20including%20North%20Carolina%2C%20where%20the%20president%20had%20his%20narrowest%20loss%20against%20Trump%20in%202020%20and%20where%20she%20was%20drawing%20even%20in%20the%20polls%20with%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'IT%20COULD%20COST%20US%20THE%20ELECTION'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENorth%20Carolina%20was%20the%20scene%20of%20her%20next%20big%20test%2C%20the%20late%20September%20Hurricane%20Helene%2C%20one%20of%20the%20deadliest%20storms%20to%20hit%20the%20U.S.%20in%20the%20last%2050%20years.%20The%20storm%20shifted%20focus%20from%20messages%20at%20the%20foundation%20of%20Harris'%20campaign%20to%20the%20handling%20of%20the%20disaster%20by%20the%20Biden-Harris%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20hit%20just%20as%20her%20lead%20was%20narrowing.%20Trump%20went%20on%20the%20attack%2C%20criticizing%20the%20Democratic%20administration's%20response%20to%20the%20disaster%20and%20tying%20it%20to%20his%20strongest%20issue%2C%20immigration.%20As%20the%20death%20count%20rose%20and%20swathes%20of%20North%20Carolina%20lay%20devastated%2C%20Trump%20amplified%20and%20spread%20falsehoods%2C%20including%20a%20claim%20that%20Harris%20spent%20disaster-assistance%20money%20on%20housing%20illegal%20migrants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20a%20recent%20request%20for%20comment%20by%20Reuters%20about%20false%20claims%20about%20how%20disaster%20funds%20were%20being%20used%2C%20the%20Trump%20campaign%20repeated%20accusations%20that%20money%20had%20been%20spent%20on%20housing%20migrants%20in%20the%20country%20illegally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarris%20cut%20short%20a%20campaign%20swing%20and%20flew%20to%20Washington%20on%20Sept.%2030%20for%20a%20briefing%20on%20Biden's%20emergency%20response.%20On%20her%20plane%2C%20three%20staffers%20sat%20on%20the%20floor%2C%20ripping%20apart%20briefing%20books%2C%20replacing%20the%20pages%20with%20new%20notes%2C%20a%20Reuters%20reporter%20witnessed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20disaster%2C%20which%20killed%20more%20than%20200%20people%2C%20marked%20a%20shift%20in%20the%20race%2C%20as%20misinformation%20around%20the%20administration's%20response%20and%20Trump's%20hard-line%20rhetoric%20on%20immigration%20gained%20traction.%20The%20baseless%20claims%20included%20that%20the%20government%20covered-up%20deaths%2C%20confiscated%20charitable%20donations%20and%20diverted%20disaster%20funds%20to%20help%20immigrants.%20Harris'%20campaign%20struggled%20to%20address%20both%20the%20false%20claims%20and%20voters'%20concerns%20about%20an%20uptick%20in%20illegal%20border%20crossings%20during%20Biden's%20presidency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20jurisdiction%20that%20illustrated%20the%20risks%20for%20Harris%20was%20Buncombe%20County%2C%20a%20North%20Carolina%20Democratic%20stronghold%20of%20about%20280%2C000%20people%20hammered%20by%20the%20storm.%20In%20its%20aftermath%2C%20Democrats%20stopped%20targeting%20potentially%20persuadable%20Republican%20voters%20there%20because%20of%20concerns%20they%20had%20become%20too%20hostile%20amid%20the%20misinformation%2C%20Kathie%20Kline%2C%20Buncombe%20County%20Democratic%20chair%2C%20told%20Reuters.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20Trump%20won%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20race%20tightened%20through%20October%2C%20and%20polls%20indicated%20a%20toss-up%2C%20alarm%20spread%20among%20Democratic%20strategists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20focused%20on%20shoring%20up%20the%20so-called%20Blue%20Wall%20of%20Democratic%20states%3A%20Michigan%2C%20Pennsylvania%20and%20Wisconsin.%20Eight%20years%20ago%2C%20when%20Trump%20beat%20Hillary%20Clinton%2C%20he%20breached%20the%20Blue%20Wall%20by%20winning%20all%20three%20states%2C%20each%20by%20less%20than%20a%20percentage%20point.%20In%202020%2C%20Biden%20won%20them%20back.%20Holding%20the%20Blue%20Wall%20now%20was%20Harris'%20best%20path%20to%20the%20White%20House%2C%20the%20strategists%20reasoned.%20But%20they%20had%20a%20problem%3A%20Michigan%20and%20the%20Gaza%20War.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMichigan's%20large%20population%20of%20Arab%20Americans%20and%20Muslims%20helped%20cement%20Biden's%202020%20victory%20in%20the%20state.%20Trump%20turned%20off%20many%20of%20these%20voters%20in%20his%20first%20term%2C%20in%20part%20by%20banning%20immigration%20to%20the%20U.S.%20from%20a%20number%20of%20Muslim%20countries%20early%20in%20his%20tenure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20race's%20final%20stretch%2C%20Muslim%20and%20Arab-American%20voters%20told%20Reuters%20they%20were%20disappointed%20Harris%20did%20not%20distance%20herself%20more%20from%20Biden's%20unwavering%20support%20of%20Israel%20during%20the%20Gaza%20war.%20In%20the%20final%20weeks%2C%20Trump%20aggressively%20courted%20their%20vote.%20Many%20said%20they%20would%20sit%20out%20the%20election%20or%20vote%20Republican.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarris%20staffers%20knew%20that%20disillusioned%20Muslim%20and%20Arab-American%20Democrats%20were%20a%20risk.%20%26quot%3BIt%20could%20cost%20us%20the%20election%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20senior%20Michigan%20operative%20for%20Harris%20in%20July.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20campaign%20ultimately%20concluded%20it%20was%20impossible%20to%20fully%20win%20back%20those%20voters.%20To%20offset%20their%20loss%2C%20campaign%20officials%20said%20they%20focused%20in%20the%20final%20weeks%20on%20marshaling%20enough%20support%20from%20union%20workers%20and%20Black%20voters%20in%20Detroit%2C%20the%20nation's%20largest%20Black-majority%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EECONOMIC%20THREATS%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20few%20issues%20threatened%20Harris%20like%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20campaign%20had%20hoped%20the%20economic%20recovery%20from%20the%20pandemic%20would%20be%20a%20winning%20issue.%20Growth%20is%20markedly%20more%20robust%20in%20the%20U.S.%20than%20in%20other%20major%20industrial%20nations.%20Stock-market%20indexes%20are%20near%20record%20highs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20the%20issue%20eroded%20Democratic%20support%20throughout%20much%20of%202024%20as%20union%20workers%20and%20non-college-educated%20white%20voters%20broke%20for%20Trump%2C%20polls%20showed.%20Sharp%20increases%20in%20housing%20and%20food%20costs%20frustrated%20voters%2C%20overshadowing%20a%20strong%20job%20market.%20Trump%20blamed%20Harris%20for%20the%20spike%20during%20her%20and%20Biden's%20time%20in%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20most%20unions%20have%20long%20supported%20Democratic%20candidates%2C%20rank-and-file%20workers%20in%20recent%20years%20have%20moved%20behind%20Trump%2C%20proving%20a%20decisive%20factor%20in%20his%20victory.%20There%20were%20some%20positive%20signs%20for%20Harris.%20The%20AFL-CIO%2C%20the%20largest%20federation%20of%20unions%2C%20saw%20a%20surge%20in%20female%20members%20supporting%20Harris%20and%20willing%20to%20volunteer%20for%20her%2C%20AFL-CIO%20President%20Liz%20Shuler%20told%20Reuters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20final%20weeks%20of%20the%20race%2C%20Harris'%20momentum%20appeared%20to%20have%20stalled%2C%20with%20polls%20showing%20her%20edge%20over%20Trump%20narrowing.%20By%20mid-October%2C%20the%20race%20was%20a%20dead%20heat%20in%20crucial%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20pronounced%20gap%20in%20polling%20between%20men%20and%20women%20had%20emerged%2C%20too.%20While%20Harris%20cut%20away%20at%20the%20Republicans'%20longstanding%20edge%20with%20white%20voters%20overall%20by%20gaining%20ground%20with%20white%20women%2C%20Trump%20appeared%20to%20be%20boosting%20his%20advantage%20with%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarris%20shifted%20strategy%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20win%20over%20more%20men%20and%20Republicans.%20The%20campaign%20dispatched%20running%20mate%20Walz%20on%20a%20tour%20in%20mid-October%20to%20reach%20male%20voters.%20Harris%20also%20held%20campaign%20events%20with%20former%20lawmaker%20Liz%20Cheney%2C%20one%20of%20Trump's%20fiercest%20Republican%20critics%20and%20one%20of%20the%20most%20prominent%20conservatives%20to%20endorse%20the%20Democrat.%20Days%20later%2C%20Trump%20suggested%20Cheney%20should%20face%20gunfi