ted%20to%20punitive%20tariffs%20in%20disputes%20with%20trade%20partners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%202024%20campaign%2C%20he%20pledged%20to%20impose%20an%20additional%2060%20percent%20import%20tariff%20on%20Chinese%20products%20and%20an%20extra%2010%20percent%20tariff%20on%20products%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaking%20into%20account%20the%20probable%20retaliatory%20measures%20from%20Beijing%20and%20Brussels%2C%20the%20impact%20on%20the%20European%20Union%20economy%20will%20be%20%24533%20billion%20through%202029%2C%20%24749%20billion%20for%20the%20United%20States%20and%20%24827%20billion%20for%20China%2C%20according%20to%20a%20study%20by%20the%20Roland%20Berger%20consulting%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20separate%20study%20by%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%20estimated%20that%20the%20impact%20on%20emerging%20market%20nations%20such%20as%20India%2C%20Indonesia%20and%20Brazil%20would%20be%20much%20less.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJamie%20Thompson%2C%20head%20of%20macroeconomic%20forecasting%20at%20London-based%20Oxford%20Economics%2C%20said%20he%20sees%20little%20shot-term%20economic%20impact%20due%20to%20the%20delays%20in%20implementing%20policies%2C%20but%20they%20could%20be%20positive%20for%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20the%20outlook%20for%202025%20is%20essentially%20unchanged%2C%20global%20growth%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20a%20little%20stronger%20in%202026%20and%202027%20on%20the%20back%20of%20the%20election%20result%2C%20as%20the%20impact%20of%20looser%20US%20fiscal%20policy%20more%20than%20offsets%20the%20drag%20from%20targeted%20tariff%20measures%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20across-the-board%20tariffs%20are%20imposed%20it%20%26quot%3Bcould%20leave%20the%20global%20economy%20around%200.75%20percent%20smaller%20--%20and%20global%20trade%20down%20some%20three%20percent%20--%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20decade%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20prospects%20